arch:property.oc:show_val: Stage 7 (not phased because of disturbance by a German survey)

Munsell 7.5YR 6/3 light brown with ashy patches and charcoal flecks in the trench center 903.356 m, 7.5YR 5/3. A few tesserae were found, as well as few sherds. Two finds were cataloged: a pierced, stone pendant (93-S-1) and a glass bead (93-G-1).

Phase XIV: Modern period marked by Bedouin activity and the accumulation of recent debris. Nazzal's dump is dug between the collapsed Porch columns on the temple Forecourt. A German survey between the temple stylobate and Forecourt results in the disturbance of these deposits.
Associated with: Locus 2, pavement, Locus 7, rubble, and Locus 11, podium platform.
Opening elevation: 904.206 m at northwest, 904.186 m at northeast, 904.356 m at center, 904.946 m at southeast.
Abandonment and subsequent accumulation of overburden.
